1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,400
<i> The Mayor is dead.</i>

2
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:13,367
<i> That's not true!</i>

3
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:17,167
<i> What happened? Your daddy!</i>

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:21,200
<i>Our beloved Mayor
Joaquin "El Hepe" Guerrero</i>

5
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:23,067
<i>has passed away after being
rushed to the hospital</i>

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>due to a severe stroke that
resulted in a brain hemorrhage.</i>

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:29,233
<i>This must be very painful
for Bobby,</i>

8
00:00:29,367 --> 00:00:30,400
<i> for my granddaughter.</i>

9
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:31,600
<i> Sergeant Enriquez.</i>

10
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:34,300
<i>Attorney, what is that woman
doing here?</i>

11
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:37,533
<i>Because she is included in
Mayor Joaquin's inheritance.</i>

12
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:40,333
<i>A resort and ten million pesos?</i>

13
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:43,300
<i>Yes, but she's thinking about
what she's going to do</i>

14
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,133
<i>with the inheritance
she inherited.</i>

15
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:46,533
<i> Mom Zondra...</i>

16
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:47,967
<i>- killed!
- Killed?</i>

17
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:49,467
<i>Oh my, I feel like
this is a hate crime.</i>

18
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,400
<i> Mom Zondra!</i>

19
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:54,600
<i>I don't know how it feels
to lose a loved one.</i>

20
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:56,700
<i>It seems like
nothing can prepare you</i>

21
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,000
<i>for the kind of pain
you're about to feel.</i>

22
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:02,833
<i>I wish he'd show up
to me even in a dream.</i>

23
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:05,367
<i>Oh, Bobby, we know someone,
a psychic.</i>

24
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,267
<i> That's great!</i>

25
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:07,633
<i> Madam Alma.</i>

26
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,333
<i> Are you ready, Mother?</i>

27
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,000
<i> Hold my hands.</i>

28
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:12,767
<i>Let's close our eyes
together, okay?</i>

29
00:01:17,133 --> 00:01:23,667
Randerzon Misa AKA Mom Zondra,
a gay performer at a comedy bar.

30
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:28,933
Imagine, he's gay
but he has a child, right?

31
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:31,367
Bok, just because he's gay

32
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,633
doesn't mean
he can't have children.

33
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,833
Yeah, there's a lot of cases
like that.

34
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:37,367
Actually, you're right.

35
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:43,067
Anyway, he has sixteen stab
wounds, all in the chest.

36
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,267
Sixteen?

37
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,500
That's a lot, Bok.

38
00:01:47,633 --> 00:01:49,167
He might have committed
a grave sin

39
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:51,600
because whoever did this to him
was really angry.

40
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:56,300
But based on what we talked
about earlier,

41
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:59,800
it seems like the whole village
is his friend.

42
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:01,700
Could this possibly
be a hate crime?

43
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:41,167
I can see him!

44
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,800
I said, close your eyes!

45
00:02:57,433 --> 00:02:59,467
He's getting closer to us!

46
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,800
I can really feel it!
This is it!

47
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:07,633
Mommy...

48
00:03:07,767 --> 00:03:09,100
Mommy?

49
00:03:13,167 --> 00:03:23,133
- Mom!
- My child!

50
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:29,033
Mom, I love you so much, Mom.

51
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:35,233
Mom, don't neglect yourself.

52
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:39,633
Yes, my dear, yes.
I won't neglect myself.

53
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:43,100
I'm in heaven, Mom.

54
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,333
Mom...

55
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:48,967
Go ahead and make amends
with grandmother.

56
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,933
Okay, my child.

57
00:03:51,067 --> 00:03:53,500
I'll end the fight between
your grandmother and I.

58
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,267
We'll patch things up.

59
00:03:55,433 --> 00:04:01,033
My child, how are you doing?
I miss you so much.

60
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:02,333
My child,

61
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:09,767
do you remember the last gift
I gave you on your birthday?

62
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,600
My child...

63
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:12,833
My child.

64
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:19,767
What happened?

65
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,867
He's gone.

66
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,900
My body can't take it anymore.
I need additional payment.

67
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,067
Linda, get some water.

68
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:30,733
I'm dizzy.

69
00:04:30,867 --> 00:04:31,967
Okay, okay.

70
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:35,233
The important thing is,
I'm happy to talk to my child.

71
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:40,700
How much?

72
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:41,933
P5,000.

73
00:04:42,067 --> 00:04:44,167
P5,000? Okay.

74
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:46,167
The spirit is too strong.

75
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:47,267
Okay.

76
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,467
Here it is.

77
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,667
Thank you very much,
Madam Alma.

78
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:01,000
Thank you very much, Mother.

79
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:04,933
Just come here
when you need something, okay?

80
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:08,133
- I'll take care of you.
- Madam Alma! You fool!

81
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,300
Opportunist! Fake!
You're a scammer!

82
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,667
You're a scammer!

83
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:16,400
Don't believe that!
That kid is lying!

84
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:19,367
Hey, my friend saw you.
He's videotaping you.

85
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:22,833
And your slurs, they're fake!
You just fooled us!

86
00:05:22,967 --> 00:05:24,867
And you didn't respect
my Mom Zondra!

87
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,233
That's not true!

88
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:28,833
Hey, give me my money back!
You're a fake!

89
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:32,133
- Give me my money back!
- Hey, this is mine!

90
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:36,367
- Give me my money!
- Hey, my money!

91
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:37,200
Stop chasing her.

92
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:39,500
Madam Alma's power is real.

93
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:41,767
If he was stabbed in front,

94
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:45,167
it means he was right
in front of him.

95
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:46,600
- They are talking.
- Policeman!

96
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,267
Policeman, arrest her!

97
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,800
Arrest that woman!

98
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,100
- Hey!
- Wait, wait, wait.

99
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:53,100
What's going on here?

100
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,233
You're really a fool.

101
00:05:55,367 --> 00:05:57,867
- What is it?
- You're a scammer!

102
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,567
Wait, wait!
What's going on here?

103
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,800
Sir, arrest that woman.
She's a scammer!

104
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:04,233
I'll file a case against her!

105
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:05,300
You're a scammer!

106
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:07,567
I hope you're scared
of what you're doing!

107
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:10,200
You're going to sue me.
Maybe I'll sue you!

108
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:11,167
Assault!

109
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:14,767
You attacked me
and it hurts so much.

110
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,467
Wait, wait...

111
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,833
Aren't you Mom Zondra's
daughter?

112
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:20,200
Yes, Sir.

113
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,133
Oh, why are you calling her
a scammer?

114
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:26,567
That's because I asked her
for help to find out

115
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,067
who really killed my mom.

116
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:31,100
And then I found out
she was just acting.

117
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:34,067
She said I could talk to mom,
but I didn't. Scammer!

118
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,367
Acting?

119
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,800
What acting are you
talking about?

120
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:38,000
Do you have proof?

121
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,867
Wait, wait a minute.
I'm getting confused with you.

122
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,833
How will Mom Zondra
tell who killed her?

123
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:47,500
Mama Zondra is dead.

124
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:50,400
Well, Sir, that's the modus
operandi of that woman.

125
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,800
She pretends to be possessed
by spirits

126
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:54,600
so that they can talk
to their families.

127
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,533
Then she will collect
payment, Sir.

128
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,433
You really are a scammer,
a fraud!

129
00:06:58,567 --> 00:06:59,633
So lock her up!

130
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:04,400
Well, Bok, her moves
are those of a scammer!

131
00:07:04,533 --> 00:07:06,600
Even her appearance,
she looks like a scammer.

132
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:13,233
Better yet, just settle this
with this kid.

133
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:16,600
No! I'm not admitting
I'm a scammer.

134
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:17,633
No.

135
00:07:17,767 --> 00:07:18,633
Okay, okay.

136
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:20,767
You only have two choices.

137
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:23,600
Return the money,
or we'll arrest you.

138
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:30,433
Wait.

139
00:07:31,967 --> 00:07:36,067
It's hard to earn money.

140
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,600
Take it.

141
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,200
Give it to me.

142
00:07:42,233 --> 00:07:43,567
Are you happy now?

143
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,733
There you go.

144
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:58,033
Hey...

145
00:07:58,933 --> 00:07:59,933
Are you okay?

146
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:11,800
Give me mom's fan.

147
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:13,667
Will you steal this, too?

148
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,700
Sir...

149
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:20,733
What happened to me?
I don't understand.

150
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:24,500
Bok, it seems like she wants
to scam us, too.

151
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:26,067
I saw something!

152
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:31,733
It's that...

153
00:08:31,867 --> 00:08:34,367
The one used for stabbing,
like a knife.

154
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,700
I...

155
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,567
Icepick! Icepick, I saw it!

156
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:39,800
- Icepick?
- I saw it, yes...

157
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:43,900
Yes. I don't know.
She was stabbed a lot of times!

158
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:45,000
It was a lot!

159
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:47,667
Sixteen...

160
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,133
- Sixteen!
- Sixteen?

161
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,433
Yes! Then the killer...

162
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:53,633
He was just around there.

163
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:54,767
He was just there.

164
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,967
Come on, my lord.
What's happening to me?

165
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,000
Am I getting karma?

166
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:03,167
What's happening to me?

167
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:06,567
Am I getting karma?

168
00:09:08,033 --> 00:09:12,633
Bok, it seems like
she outsmarted us.

169
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:15,867
She just walked away like that.

170
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,167
She got away.

171
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,433
How did she know that?

172
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,433
What's that?

173
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:33,833
It's hard to make money.

174
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:39,967
And where would I get the money?

175
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,700
And there are a lot of ghosts.

176
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,200
She'll file a case against me?

177
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:50,233
What if I file a lawsuit
against her, too?

178
00:09:50,367 --> 00:09:52,367
I just want to make
some money...

179
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:07,200
<i> Alma!</i>

180
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,300
What's that?

181
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:25,267
Am I going crazy?

182
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,767
Why can I hear people?

183
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,100
Oh my...

184
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:33,733
- But I ate earlier.
- Alma...

185
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:44,967
Oh my, what's happening to me?

186
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:49,800
What's happening to me?

187
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:55,267
Oh, Bok...

188
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:59,067
Why do you seem uneasy
about what Alma said?

189
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:03,200
No, Bok, I was just really
surprised.

190
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,533
I can't believe it.

191
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:07,100
The details she said
are exactly the same.

192
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:12,600
Icepick, sixteen stab wounds.

193
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:14,367
How would she know that?

194
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,733
Okay, in fairness to Alma.

195
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:20,167
But, Bok, I just have a doubt.

196
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:25,133
I feel like I know where Alma
got that information.

197
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,400
Where?

198
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,433
Noble!

199
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:35,533
How are you?

200
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,533
Well, let me just ask you.

201
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:44,767
Are you telling your reporter
girlfriend about the information

202
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:48,667
about Mom Zondra's case?

203
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:49,967
Sir, no.

204
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:52,800
What do you mean no?

205
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:55,333
You're not telling her,
or she's not your girlfriend?

206
00:11:56,867 --> 00:12:00,800
Sir, I'm not telling her.

207
00:12:02,367 --> 00:12:03,633
So she's your girlfriend?

208
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:08,767
Noble, Noble,
you're learning from me!

209
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:11,767
What now, Bok?

210
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,700
Noble didn't say anything.

211
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:19,500
How would Alma know the contents
of Mom Zondra's files?

212
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:22,533
How could she say that?

213
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:42,733
Here, Malou, let your husband
drink this.

214
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,933
It's guaranteed to bring back
the sweetness of your love.

215
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:48,067
Are you sure?
Is your potion legit?

216
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:50,033
Of course, it's legit!

217
00:12:50,167 --> 00:12:51,467
How much is that?

218
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,767
Only five hundred.

219
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,967
That's expensive!

220
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,733
Can't it be just P350?

221
00:12:55,867 --> 00:12:58,200
Madam, P350, they say.

222
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:02,300
Malou, the ingredients
are from Romania,

223
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:05,200
so it's really expensive.

224
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,500
Really?
From Romania?

225
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:09,367
Okay, okay, I'll buy it.

226
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,000
I'll buy it.
It looks effective.

227
00:13:14,433 --> 00:13:15,200
Here, here.

228
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:18,733
One, two, three, four, five.

229
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:19,767
Five hundred.

230
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,033
I'll buy it.
Thank you.

231
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,633
Thank you very much, Malou.

232
00:13:24,767 --> 00:13:25,800
Here.

233
00:13:26,933 --> 00:13:30,733
If you need anything else,
just let me know.

234
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:34,833
Okay, Madam Alma, okay.
Thank you, thank you.

235
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:38,400
I'll just walk her out.

236
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:40,033
I'll just buy something
for a while.

237
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:06,200
Alma, help me.

238
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:09,400
The killer need to be caught.

239
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,467
He might kill someone else.

240
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:26,433
- Help me, Alma, Alma...
- Get away, you animal!

241
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:56,200
Oh, my Lord.

242
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:59,133
<i> Help me, Alma.</i>

243
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,367
Help me.

244
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:13,267
What's that?

245
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:15,933
What's going on?

246
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,300
What's going on?

247
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:24,333
I don't know!
What are you doing here?

248
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:30,333
I'm here to ask you
if you know Mom Zondra,

249
00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:33,400
the victim of the icepick
murder?

250
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,033
Don't drag me into that.

251
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:39,133
I don't want to get involved
in that case of yours!

252
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:40,433
Alma,

253
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:44,400
I need to know how you found out
about the details of her murder.

254
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,067
I don't know!

255
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,833
I just saw it in my mind,
like visions!

256
00:15:48,967 --> 00:15:51,500
If you don't want to believe me,
there's nothing I can do.

257
00:15:51,633 --> 00:15:53,733
I didn't want
what's happening to me.

258
00:15:55,967 --> 00:15:57,200
I'm sorry.

259
00:15:57,333 --> 00:16:02,333
Yes, I'm a scammer, but I feel
like I'm getting karma.

260
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:05,067
That Mom Zondra is showing
herself to me!

261
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,533
Is she showing herself to you?

262
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:08,567
Yes, she's showing herself
to me.

263
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:09,967
She's begging for help.

264
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:12,433
Maybe the killer
will kill someone else.

265
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:17,233
Okay, I'm going
to close now, Sir.

266
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:19,000
You can now leave.

267
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:23,133
Okay, okay,
I won't bother you anymore,

268
00:16:23,267 --> 00:16:25,067
but if you find out
anymore details...

269
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:28,733
let me know.

270
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:29,900
Call me.

271
00:16:32,567 --> 00:16:33,800
Oh, okay, Sir, thank you.

272
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:37,167
Sorry, I'm really feeling bad.

273
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,400
Okay.

274
00:16:48,767 --> 00:16:52,367
Mom Zondra, don't show yourself
to me anymore, okay?

275
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:02,200
I still can't believe

276
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:06,200
why your daddy gave that Bobby
an inheritance.

277
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:11,533
You know, I'm sure he did it
out of guilt for cheating.

278
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,067
Mom...

279
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,367
Let's not talk about it anymore.

280
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:22,333
Let's just move on, okay?

281
00:17:22,467 --> 00:17:25,267
What do you think of my outfit?

282
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,700
Is it okay
for my oath-taking?

283
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:31,633
- It's fine.
- It's fine.

284
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,733
Yes, Faye?

285
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:37,267
Why does it seem like you're not
grieving over daddy's death?

286
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:42,867
What do you mean?

287
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,500
If it's not about inheritance,

288
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:47,200
you're talking
about your outfit.

289
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:51,767
Mommy, it's only been days
since daddy was buried.

290
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:55,067
Faye, we have different means
of coping.

291
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,967
Really, Glen?

292
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:59,333
Yours is so different.

293
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:00,733
Because out of the three of us,

294
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:02,433
you seem to be the one
who is least affected

295
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:03,767
by daddy's passing.

296
00:18:05,767 --> 00:18:07,033
Faye...

297
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:09,300
Let her leave, Glen.

298
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:11,833
It's her way of dealing with it.

299
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:33,833
- Miss Faye, condolences.
- Condolences, Miss Faye.

300
00:18:33,967 --> 00:18:35,933
What brings you here?

301
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:38,933
Where is Bobby?

302
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,333
Sorry, she's still on leave.

303
00:18:42,467 --> 00:18:44,533
What can we do for you?

304
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:46,567
I just want to talk to her.

305
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:50,433
You can text her.
Maybe she'll reply to you.

306
00:18:50,567 --> 00:18:53,700
- Okay. Thank you.
- Okay, Miss Faye.

307
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:54,967
Hey, Faye.

308
00:18:58,567 --> 00:18:59,900
Hey, how are you?

309
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:04,933
To be honest,
I'm not really okay yet.

310
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:10,400
I wanted to invite Bobby,
but she's still on leave.

311
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,167
You want to hang out?

312
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:17,133
I know a billiards place nearby.

313
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:19,567
Okay, please.
Let's just go out.

314
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,433
Okay, let's meet later.

315
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,033
- Come on.
- Okay.

316
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:26,067
Okay, Faye.

317
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:36,200
Doc Cecilia,
you have a visitor.

318
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,233
- Faye?
- Hi, Cecilia.

319
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:41,533
What are you doing here?

320
00:19:41,667 --> 00:19:43,567
Are you with Glen?

321
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:45,033
Ah, no.

322
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:47,233
I was just going to visit Bobby.

323
00:19:47,367 --> 00:19:49,767
But, she's still on leave today.

324
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:52,900
Well, Lieutenant Garcia
mentioned that you were here.

325
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,300
So I visited you.

326
00:19:54,433 --> 00:19:55,333
You're so sweet.

327
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:58,100
Teach your brother
to be sweet too.

328
00:19:58,233 --> 00:19:59,967
Cecilia, if you're free,

329
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:02,700
my friends are inviting me
to go out later.

330
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:04,300
Maybe you want to come along?

331
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:07,900
Sure!

332
00:20:08,033 --> 00:20:10,533
So we can bond.

333
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,733
But are your friends okay
with that?

334
00:20:12,867 --> 00:20:16,100
That's okay, Cecilia.
The more, the merrier.

335
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:22,533
Yes?

336
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:26,067
Lieutenant Garcia,
do you want to come too?

337
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:31,400
I'm a busy person,
but I'll check with my schedule.

338
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:32,400
Wait a minute, huh?

339
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:39,533
I'm okay, I can but can I have
an extra one?

340
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,067
The more, the merrier, right?

341
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:51,800
Where is that?

342
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:52,933
I don't know.

343
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:53,933
It's Sir Tonyo!

344
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:55,500
Sir Tonyo!

345
00:20:55,633 --> 00:20:56,567
- What are you doing here?
- Hi, Sir.

346
00:20:58,633 --> 00:20:59,700
Because of work.

347
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,800
Hey guys, why are you here?

348
00:21:01,933 --> 00:21:04,600
Do you know anything
about this place?

349
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:06,967
We're looking for Madam Alma.

350
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:08,600
Yes.

351
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,433
The fortune teller?

352
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:11,833
Yes, that's her.

353
00:21:11,967 --> 00:21:15,033
Do you know
where we can find her?

354
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:17,933
Oh my, she's out of service.
She's not feeling well.

355
00:21:18,067 --> 00:21:19,100
Do you know her, too?

356
00:21:19,233 --> 00:21:20,700
Yes.

357
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:23,500
Wait, why are you looking
for her?

358
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:26,567
Well, it's for Bobby.

359
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:30,433
Well, Bobby wants to talk
to Mayor Joaquin.

360
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:32,400
Is that so?

361
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:37,900
By the way, how is Bobby?

362
00:21:38,033 --> 00:21:39,900
She's not answering my calls.

363
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,700
Why are you only calling her?

364
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:47,267
Why not visit her?

365
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:51,400
Well, she said she needed space.

366
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:53,867
So that's what I'm giving her.

367
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,867
My god, Sir Tonyo.

368
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:56,867
You're such a good cop,

369
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,133
but as a lover, oh my,
you're so weak.

370
00:21:59,267 --> 00:22:03,467
-True! You're being too literal.
- Yes.

371
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,000
What do you mean?

372
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:12,500
Bobby!

373
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,133
You have a visitor.

374
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:17,400
Who?

375
00:22:17,533 --> 00:22:18,600
There.

376
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,167
Bobby...

377
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:23,000
Tonyo...

378
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,200
Bobby, I'm sorry.

379
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:28,333
I know you said
you wanted to be alone...

380
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:31,800
But I'm really worried
about you.

381
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,867
Oh my god, Bobby.
Don't play hard to get.

382
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:37,600
Yes, and we know you want
to see Sir Tonyo.

383
00:22:42,233 --> 00:22:44,133
Tonyo, I'm sorry too.

384
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,967
I don't know what to do.

385
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,267
I thought of something.

386
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:55,167
- What?
- Bobby, since you're sad,

387
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:58,433
what if we go to a comedy bar!

388
00:22:58,567 --> 00:22:59,467
Right?

389
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:03,267
Yeah, so Bobby can laugh.

390
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:07,200
What, Sir Tonyo, Bobby?

391
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:09,067
Are you down later?

392
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:14,467
How about you, Bobby?

393
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:17,933
Okay.

394
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:20,133
I'm sorry again, Tonyo.

395
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:28,433
Let's go.

396
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:33,367
- I'm thrilled.
- Yes, I know.

397
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:41,367
- I'm so thrilled.
- I'm jealous.

398
00:24:00,967 --> 00:24:03,833
Didn't you understand me,
or are you just teasing me?

399
00:24:03,967 --> 00:24:05,400
You've been touching her
for a while now.

400
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:06,367
Wait, wait, wait.

401
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,600
Hey, the girl doesn't like you.

402
00:24:07,733 --> 00:24:10,767
- You're a jerk.
- That's enough!

403
00:24:10,900 --> 00:24:13,400
You didn't say you were good
at hitting.

404
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:14,667
I'll accept your teasing,
but not this.

405
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:18,367
You are even using me to make
other girls jealous?

406
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,233
Do you think so low of me?

407
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:22,033
Let's go to Tootsie
in the dressing room.

408
00:24:22,167 --> 00:24:23,833
- Let's bring Bobby.
- She's all alone here.

409
00:24:23,967 --> 00:24:24,833
Oh, okay.

410
00:24:24,967 --> 00:24:26,767
- Hey, Tootsie!
- Gay!
